'''Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha''' (金刀比羅宮東京分社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都|qq=draft}} {{ill|Bunkyo|ja|文京区|qq=draft}}. It is a branch of {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅宮|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|qq=draft}} {{ill|Nakatado District|ja|仲多度郡|qq=draft}} {{ill|Kotohira|ja|琴平町|qq=draft}}. The shrine's emblem is a circle with gold.

== {{nihongo|Worshipped deities|祭神|Saijin}} ==
* {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神|lt=Ōmononushi deity|lt_ja=大物主神|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Ukano Mitama|ja|ウカノミタマ|lt=Ukano Mitama deity|lt_ja=倉稲魂神|qq=draft}}

== History ==
{{ill|1819|ja|1819th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Bunsei era|ja|文政|qq=draft}} 2 year), a local head ({{ill|Nagushi|ja|名主|qq=draft}}) named Itabashi Shizaemon from {{ill|Itabashi-shuku|ja|板橋宿|lt=Shimoitabashi-shuku Kamijuku|lt_ja=下板橋宿上宿|qq=draft}}, enshrined {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅宮|lt=Konpira Great Authority|lt_ja=金毘羅大権現|qq=draft}} on his property as a family shrine. In {{ill|1880|ja|1880th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft}} 13 year), it was officially recognized as a {{ill|Mukaku-sha|ja|無格社|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft}}.

In {{ill|1888|ja|1888th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft}} 21 year), the shrine was relocated to {{ill|Kanda Izumicho|ja|神田和泉町|qq=draft}} and added to the peripheral shrines directly under {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅宮|qq=draft}}.

In {{ill|1890|ja|1890th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft}} 23 year), it was moved to {{ill|Furuishiba|ja|古石場|lt=Fukagawa Furuishibacho|lt_ja=深川古石場町|qq=draft}}. Both the {{ill|Great Kantō earthquake|ja|関東大震災|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Tokyo air raid|ja|東京大空襲|qq=draft}} burned the structures, and after the war, the sacred spirit was transferred to the Asahi Shrine of the main shrine in {{ill|Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐国|lt=Sanuki|lt_ja=讃岐|qq=draft}}.

In {{ill|1956|ja|1956th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Shōwa era|ja|昭和|qq=draft}} 31 year), from Matsudaira Yoriaki (Count) of the former {{ill|Takamatsu Domain|ja|高松藩|qq=draft}}, belonging to the {{ill|Takamatsu Matsudaira Family|ja|高松松平家|lt=Tatsudaira family|lt_ja=松平家|qq=draft}}, a donation of the land of the former {{ill|Kamiyashiki|ja|上屋敷|qq=draft}} of the Sanuki Takamatsu Domain was received. This land, previously used for establishing the {{ill|Suidobashi (Kandagawa)|ja|水道橋 (神田川)|lt=Suidobashi|lt_ja=水道橋|qq=draft}} {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft}}, founded in {{ill|1793|ja|1793rd year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Kansei era|ja|寛政|qq=draft}} 5 year), enabled the two shrines to be enshrined together, and the relocation and restoration were completed in {{ill|1964|ja|1964th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Shōwa era|ja|昭和|qq=draft}} 39 year).

== Annual Festival ==
* January 10 - Hatsu-jūnichi Festival
* February 3 - Setsubun Festival (bean throwing by wrestlers from {{ill|Sado Gakatake stable|ja|佐渡ヶ嶽部屋|qq=draft}})
* May 19–20 - Annual Festival Days

== Location Information ==
; Location
: {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都|qq=draft}} {{ill|Bunkyo|ja|文京区|qq=draft}} Hongo 1-5-11
; Transportation
:* Railway
:** {{ill|Suidobashi Station|ja|水道橋駅|qq=draft}} (5-minute walk from alighting at {{ill|Chuo-Sobu Local Line|ja|中央・総武緩行線|lt=JR Chuo Line|lt_ja=JR中央線|qq=draft}} and 3-minute walk from alighting at {{ill|Toei Mita Line|ja|都営地下鉄三田線|qq=draft}})

