{{infobox Shinto shrine |Name = {{ill|Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha|ja|金刀比羅宮東京分社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha|qq=}} |image = [[File:FNic7yqaIAYd4RS.png|240px]] |address = [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo Metropolis]] [[:en:Bunkyō|Bunkyo]] {{ill|Hongo|ja|本郷|lt=Hongo (Bunkyo)|lt_ja=本郷 (文京区)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hongo|qq=}}1-5-11 |Coordinates = {{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|35|42|13.5|N|139|45|21.5|E|display=inline,title}} |Deities = [[:en:Ōmononushi|Ōmononushi deity]], [[:en:Emperor Sutoku|Emperor Sutoku]] |Status = |Founded = [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei era]] 2 year ([[:en:1819|1819]]) |Main Hall = |Also known as = {{ill|Kotohira shrines|lt=Kotohira shrines|lt=Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira Shrine|qq=}} |Memorabilia = |Annual Festival = May 20 |Rituals = |Map = {{Location map|Japan Tokyo city|lat_deg=35|lat_min=42|lat_sec=13.5|lon_deg=139|lon_min=45|lon_sec=21.5|label={{ill|Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha|ja|金刀比羅宮東京分社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha|qq=}}|position=top|width=200|float=center|caption=|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=20}} {{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=13|marker=religious-shinto|frame-align=center|frame-width=200|coord={{coord|35|42|13.5|N|139|45|21.5|E}}}} }}
'''Konpira-gu Tokyo Bunsha''' (金刀比羅宮東京分社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo Metropolis]] [[:en:Bunkyō|Bunkyo]]. It is a branch of [[:en:Kotohira-gū|Konpira Shrine]] located in [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]] [[:en:Nakatado District, Kagawa|Nakatado District]] [[:en:Kotohira, Kagawa|Kotohira]]. The shrine's emblem is a circle with gold.
== {{nihongo|Worshipped deities|祭神|Saijin}} == * {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神|lt=Ōmononushi deity|lt_ja=大物主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=}} * [[:en:Ukanomitama|Ukano Mitama deity]]
== History == [[:en:1819|1819]] ([[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei era]] 2 year), a local head ({{ill|Nagushi|ja|名主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagushi|qq=}}) named Itabashi Shizaemon from [[:en:Itabashi-shuku|Shimoitabashi-shuku Kamijuku]], enshrined [[:en:Kotohira-gū|Konpira Great Authority]] on his property as a family shrine. In [[:en:1880|1880]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 13 year), it was officially recognized as a {{ill|Mukaku-sha|ja|無格社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mukaku-sha|qq=}} and {{ill|Kotohira shrines|lt=Kotohira shrines|lt=Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira Shrine|qq=}}.
In [[:en:1888|1888]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 21 year), the shrine was relocated to [[:en:Izumichō, Chiyoda, Tokyo|Kanda Izumicho]] and added to the peripheral shrines directly under [[:en:Kotohira-gū|Konpira Shrine]].
In [[:en:1890|1890]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 23 year), it was moved to {{ill|Furuishiba|ja|古石場|lt=Fukagawa Furuishibacho|lt_ja=深川古石場町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furuishiba|qq=}}. Both the {{ill|Great Kantō earthquake|ja|関東大震災|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Kantō earthquake|qq=}} and the [[:en:Bombing of Tokyo|Tokyo air raid]] burned the structures, and after the war, the sacred spirit was transferred to the Asahi Shrine of the main shrine in [[:en:Sanuki Province|Sanuki]].
In [[:en:1956|1956]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Shōwa era]] 31 year), from Matsudaira Yoriaki (Count) of the former [[:en:Takamatsu Domain|Takamatsu Domain]], belonging to the {{ill|Takamatsu Matsudaira Family|ja|高松松平家|lt=Tatsudaira family|lt_ja=松平家|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsu Matsudaira Family|qq=}}, a donation of the land of the former {{ill|Kamiyashiki|ja|上屋敷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiyashiki|qq=}} of the Sanuki Takamatsu Domain was received. This land, previously used for establishing the {{ill|Suidobashi (Kandagawa)|ja|水道橋 (神田川)|lt=Suidobashi|lt_ja=水道橋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suidobashi (Kandagawa)|qq=}} {{ill|Kotohira shrines|lt=Kotohira shrines|lt=Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira Shrine|qq=}}, founded in [[:en:1793|1793]] ([[:en:Kansei|Kansei era]] 5 year), enabled the two shrines to be enshrined together, and the relocation and restoration were completed in [[:en:1964|1964]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Shōwa era]] 39 year).
== Annual Festival == * January 10 - Hatsu-jūnichi Festival * February 3 - Setsubun Festival (bean throwing by wrestlers from [[:en:Sadogatake stable|Sado Gakatake stable]]) * May 19–20 - Annual Festival Days
== Location Information == ; Location : [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo Metropolis]] [[:en:Bunkyō|Bunkyo]] Hongo 1-5-11 ; Transportation :* Railway :** [[:en:Suidōbashi Station|Suidobashi Station]] (5-minute walk from alighting at [[:en:Chūō-Sōbu Line|JR Chuo Line]] and 3-minute walk from alighting at [[:en:Toei Mita Line|Toei Mita Line]])
