== History ==
[[:en:1819|1819]] ([[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei era]] 2 year), a local head ({{ill|Nagushi|ja|名主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagushi|qq=}}) named Itabashi Shizaemon from [[:en:Itabashi-shuku|Shimoitabashi-shuku Kamijuku]], enshrined [[:en:Kotohira-gū|Konpira Great Authority]] on his property as a family shrine. In [[:en:1880|1880]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 13 year), it was officially recognized as a {{ill|Mukaku-sha|ja|無格社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mukaku-sha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}} and {{ill|Kotohira shrines|lt=Kotohira shrines|lt=Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira Shrine|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}.

In [[:en:1888|1888]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 21 year), the shrine was relocated to [[:en:Izumichō, Chiyoda, Tokyo|Kanda Izumicho]] and added to the peripheral shrines directly under [[:en:Kotohira-gū|Konpira Shrine]].

In [[:en:1890|1890]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 23 year), it was moved to {{ill|Furuishiba|ja|古石場|lt=Fukagawa Furuishibacho|lt_ja=深川古石場町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furuishiba|qq=}}. Both the {{ill|Great Kantō earthquake|ja|関東大震災|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Kantō earthquake|qq=}} and the [[:en:Bombing of Tokyo|Tokyo air raid]] burned the structures, and after the war, the sacred spirit was transferred to the Asahi Shrine of the main shrine in [[:en:Sanuki Province|Sanuki]].

In [[:en:1956|1956]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Shōwa era]] 31 year), from Matsudaira Yoriaki (Count) of the former [[:en:Takamatsu Domain|Takamatsu Domain]], belonging to the {{ill|Takamatsu Matsudaira Family|ja|高松松平家|lt=Tatsudaira family|lt_ja=松平家|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsu Matsudaira Family|qq=}}, a donation of the land of the former {{ill|Kamiyashiki|ja|上屋敷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiyashiki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 武家屋敷}} of the Sanuki Takamatsu Domain was received. This land, previously used for establishing the {{ill|Suidobashi (Kandagawa)|ja|水道橋 (神田川)|lt=Suidobashi|lt_ja=水道橋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suidobashi (Kandagawa)|qq=}} {{ill|Kotohira shrines|lt=Kotohira shrines|lt=Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konpira Shrine|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}, founded in [[:en:1793|1793]] ([[:en:Kansei|Kansei era]] 5 year), enabled the two shrines to be enshrined together, and the relocation and restoration were completed in [[:en:1964|1964]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Shōwa era]] 39 year).

